        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 7:25AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 725 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Panola Mountain State
Park, or 10 miles southeast of Decatur, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Conyers, Covington, Jonesboro, Stockbridge, Morrow, Oxford, Lithonia,
Porterdale, Walnut Grove, Jersey, Lakeview Estates, Georgia
International Horse Park, Rex, Belmont, Arabia Mountain, Big Haynes
Creek Park, Hidden Valley Park, Kelleytown, Oak Hill, and Snapfinger.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
